article.description: UTEP advances in C-USA tourney, beats FIU 83-71
article.headline: UTEP advances in C-USA tourney, beats FIU 83-71
article.linkText: UTEP advances in C-USA tourney, beats FIU 83-71
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Julian Washburn led five players in double figures with 19 points and second-seeded UTEP advanced past tenth-seeded Florida International 83-71 in the Conference USA tournament on Thursday. UTEP (22-9) will face sixth-seeded Middle Tennessee, which knocked off No. 3 seed Old Dominion 59-52 on Thursday, in the semifinals on Friday. Vince Hunter had 16 points, Omega Harris was 5 of 5 with three 3-pointers for 15 points, Earvin Morris scored 14 and Cedrick Lang added 12 points and eight rebounds. UTEP shot 61 percent and made 8 of 12 3-point attempts. UTEP got back-to-back 3-pointers midway through the first half from Morris and Washburn to go up by eight, and then scored the final six points of the half to lead 47-33 at the break. The Miners' lead reached 20 early in the second half after a 12-5 run. Florida International (16-17) was led by Dennis Mavin with 20 points. Adrian Diaz added 13 points and five steals.
